Actor Yul Edochie has paid tributes to his two wives, referring to them as “wives of a King.” It started with his reaction to the post of his first wife, May Edochie, calling her the CEO extraordinaeire. He said: “Lovely look. My CEO Extraordinaire. My wife. The wife of a King.”   Actor Afolayan laments ‘dead’ economy     I’ve never felt insecure about my body –…     Jaro Davids dedicates ‘Obong of Sankwala’ to Obanliku LG   Moments later, he was in the comment section of his second wife Judy Austin, reiterating her as wife of a King too. He lavished her with praises in Igbo language, stating “IJELE!. Nwuye Odogwu. Nwuyem. Wife of a King.”